---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Teaching" description="Teaching experience of Christina M. Bradley">
  <div class="teaching-page">
    <h1>Teaching</h1>

    <!-- ── Sole Instructor ── -->
    <h2>Sole Instructor</h2>

    <div class="course-list">
      <div class="course">
        <div class="course-header">
          <div>
            <h3>Weekend MBA 612 — Bargaining &amp; Influence Skills: Negotiating Strategy in a Global Economy</h3>
            <p class="course-meta">Spring/Summer Semester 2023, 2024, &amp; 2025 &bull; University of Michigan, Stephen M. Ross School of Business, Ann Arbor, MI</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="course-details">
          <div class="detail-row">
            <span class="detail-label">Enrollment</span>
            <span>32 WMBA students (2023) &bull; 35 students (2024) &bull; 30 students (2025)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="detail-row">
            <span class="detail-label">Ratings</span>
            <span>
              <span class="rating">4.6/5.0</span> (2023) &bull;
              <span class="rating">4.7/5.0</span> (2024) &bull;
              <span class="rating">4.7/5.0</span> (2025)
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="course">
        <div class="course-header">
          <div>
            <h3>MO 300 — Behavioral Theories in Management</h3>
            <p class="course-meta">Fall Semester 2021 &bull; University of Michigan, Stephen M. Ross School of Business, Ann Arbor, MI</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="course-details">
          <div class="detail-row">
            <span class="detail-label">Enrollment</span>
            <span>78 undergraduates</span>
          </div>
          <div class="detail-row">
            <span class="detail-label">Rating</span>
            <span><span class="rating">4.9/5.0</span></span>
          </div>
          <div class="detail-row">
            <span class="detail-label">Award</span>
            <span>Winner of the Thomas W. Leabo Memorial Award for Academic and Teaching Excellence, Ross School of Business 2020–21 <em>(recognizes top 1–2 student instructors in Ross)</em></span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── Teaching Assistantships ── -->
    <h2>Teaching Assistantships</h2>
    <ul class="ta-list">
      <li>
        <span class="ta-year">2022–2024</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Negotiation Strategy</strong> — Full-time MBA<br />
          <span class="ta-instructor">with Professor Sanchez-Burks</span>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="ta-year">2020–2024</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Leading Organizational Change</strong> — Executive MBA<br />
          <span class="ta-instructor">with Professor Sanchez-Burks</span>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="ta-year">2019</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Leading People and Organizations</strong> — Full-time MBA<br />
          <span class="ta-instructor">with Professor Dave Mayer</span>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="ta-year">2019</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Human Behavior and Organizations: Managing for Excellence in Work Organizations</strong> — Full-time MBA<br />
          <span class="ta-instructor">with Professor Wayne Baker</span>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <!-- ── Course Evaluation Comments ── -->
    <h2>Course Evaluation Comments</h2>
    <div class="quotes">
      <blockquote>
        "Christina Bradley is WONDERFUL! She cares so much about her students and will do anything to support them. She deserves all the praise in the world."
      </blockquote>
      <blockquote>
        "Christina Bradley was a power house instructor. Her energy was always bright and encouraging, and she is a master facilitator. It is clear she listened to our feedback and input, and has a fine skill at connecting and synthesizing thoughts shared across not only different people, but carrying them through from past courses as well."
      </blockquote>
      <blockquote>
        "Professor Bradley was so so amazing. So receptive to feedback and always willing to change based on our preferences. She also did such a good job keeping people engaged and making everyone feel acknowledged whenever they provided a response. Overall amazing!!"
      </blockquote>
      <blockquote>
        "Christina Bradley is an absolute joy :) I looked forward to MO solely because I knew her enthusiasm and excitement would genuinely brighten my day and get me interested in content"
      </blockquote>
      <blockquote>
        "Very fun, very well structured, very informative. I loved all the simulation games we played. Professor Bradley has to be one of the nicest people I have ever met. She went out of her way to ensure that we always knew what was expected of us in the course, and I appreciated how active she was in my learning process this semester."
      </blockquote>
      <blockquote>
        "Professor Bradley did a great job with this class. She was extremely energetic, interested, and engaging each day. She did an awesome job communicating each day with actionable items for us, and even had some mid semester feedback opportunities for us to give to her, and she listened and changed her style based on this feedback. She is awesome!"
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .teaching-page {
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  h1 {
    margin-bottom: 1.1rem;
  }

  /* ── Courses ── */
  .course-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.75rem;
  }

  .course {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--bg-card);
  }

  .course-header {
    padding: 1.1rem 1.25rem 0.75rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: #f7f6f2;
  }

  .course-header h3 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--navy);
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
  }

  .course-meta {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-light);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .course-details {
    padding: 0.9rem 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .detail-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    align-items: baseline;
  }

  .detail-label {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-light);
    min-width: 6rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .rating {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--navy);
  }

  /* ── TA list ── */
  .ta-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.9rem;
  }

  .ta-list li {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    align-items: baseline;
  }

  .ta-year {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 500;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 5.5rem;
  }

  .ta-instructor {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--text-light);
  }

  /* ── Quotes ── */
  .quotes {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  blockquote {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-light);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    padding: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem 1.25rem;
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
